		<td><b>Re: How to start making music for my game?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think Drew Carey said this...how to write a joke...first, write 20 bad jokes. Then take the least bad joke, and rewrite it over and over until it's a good joke.<br /><br />When I try to write a song, I will sit and goof around on the piano for an hour, until I have at least 1 line of decent melody, then I try to play 20+ variations on that melody, then I write it down (or record it), and spend weeks refining and refining until it's either a song, or (more often) a piece of crap that I toss in the garbage.<br /><br />And, listen to good songs / look at good famitracker files. See how other people do it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


